Title: Restoring Lorentz Invariance in Classical N=2 String
Authors: Stefano Bellucci, Anton Galajinsky (INFN-Frascati)
Comments: 17 pages, LaTex
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B606 (2001) 119-136
\\
  We study classical N=2 string within the framework of the N=4 topological
formalism by Berkovits and Vafa. Special emphasis is put on the demonstration
of a classical equivalence of the theories and the construction of an action
for the N=4 topological string. The SO(2,2) Lorentz invariance missing in the
conventional Brink--Schwarz action for the N=2 string is restored in the N=4
topological action.
